#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga "
msgstr "2. Lay Followers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Navakammikasutta "
msgstr "17. The Builder "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.180, pts2ed1.387, sc1
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: In this sutta I use jungle for vana to (hopefully) bring out the puns
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe kammantaṃ kārāpeti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Builder was doing some building work in that jungle thicket. "

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ sālarukkhamūle nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "He saw the Buddha sitting down cross-legged at the root of a certain sal tree, with his body straight, and mindfulness established right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.4"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Seeing this, it occurred to him, "

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.5"
msgid "“ahaṃ kho imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe kammantaṃ kārāpento ramāmi. "
msgstr "“I enjoy doing this building work here in the jungle. "

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo kiṃ kārāpento ramatī”ti? "
msgstr "I wonder what the ascetic Gotama enjoys doing?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Bhāradvāja the Builder went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.1"
msgid "“Ke nu kammantā karīyanti, "
msgstr "“What kind of work do you do "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.2"
msgid "bhikkhu sālavane tava; "
msgstr "as a mendicant in the sal jungle? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.3"
msgid "Yadekako araññasmiṃ, "
msgstr "How do you find enjoyment "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.4"
msgid "ratiṃ vindati gotamo”ti. "
msgstr "alone in the wilderness, Gotama?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.1"
msgid "“Na me vanasmiṃ karaṇīyamatthi, "
msgstr "“There’s nothing I need to do in the jungle; "

# NOTE: Accepting visukkham, see BB’s note. This is, in addition, supported by SA2 96, which has 一切盡枯摧
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.2"
msgid "Ucchinnamūlaṃ me vanaṃ visūkaṃ; "
msgstr "my jungle’s cut down at the root, it’s withered away. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.3"
msgid "Svāhaṃ vane nibbanatho visallo, "
msgstr "With jungle cleared and free of thorns, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.4"
msgid "Eko rame aratiṃ vippahāyā”ti. "
msgstr "I enjoy being alone in the jungle, having given up discontent.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.388, sc4
msgctxt "sn7.17:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Builder said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.17:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama … "

msgctxt "sn7.17:4.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
